Mosaic Notes: Helebar. Mosaic deployed just outside of lagoon/barrier reef about 150m off of reef. The location of mosaic is just to the left of the cut into the small lagoon. The WP is at the start of the mosaic. Mosaic ends on steep drop off almost vertical! The 10m x 10m area is the only flat area available at the site.

Kitzha. BZ-Mosaic, Stuart-Measure. Mosaic set up west of small bay where a small mooring float was in 20'. The bay had a sand/rubble middle and mosaic was deployed just to the right as you look towards the shore. Swim just around the corner of the coral slope to find the reef flat with steep drop off seaward.
Kolombangara. Mosaic just off of sandy beach steep slope. Inshore bearing 100 degrees and center line of mosaic runs 0/180 degrees.

Tetepare. Rubble slope, principally dead Acropora branches tumbling down the slope. Mosaic covers two big boulders, each with coral and other invertebrate growth. Ends on the downslope side with a steep slope.

Tetepare. Mosaic set just outside of ranger station at the point. Moderate current / surge. Mosaic on top of spur in a spur and groove habitat. Center pins follow 100 / 280 degree line. Deploy SBE-56 serial number 56-04352 outside of ranger station on the forereef. Instrument was deployed in spure and groove habitat on south edge/groove wall just seaward of large Porities sp head.

Biche. Mosaic is 5-10m west (left) looking toward shore of GPS marker Directly outside of small river mouth/rubble boulders. Fish Transects laid out along ledge/wall across mosaic plot and away from small bay.

Biche. Start of mosaic just north of large (~8m diameter) Porites lobabta colony and at the base of steep wall from shore. Deployed SBE_56 on the seaward side of a large diameter (~8m) Porites lobata colony. Site location was at the base of the steep wall from shore just in from of village and south of landing area towards the point.

Kavache. Mosaic completed on outter reef of Zaira village. No real distinguishable reef features so the GPS waypoint is the best reference point. The center line of the mosaic was deployed in a 70/230 degree orientation along the reef slope. Inshore bearing is 320 degrees.

Kolombangara. Mosaic on rubble slope just outside of village point and inside MPA. Various rocky outcrops with Acropora growth 30-45 degree slope down. Inshore bearing 75 degrees. STR deployed at same site as mosaic and deployed on a rock outcropping along steep slope amongst rubble. Serial number 56-04355

Mbulo. Mosaic is located in the center of two coral bommies that come to just below the surface. Site is a populare dive site and has a small surface mooring in the shallows. SBE-56 deployed to the left (south) side of the mosaic plot on the base of the coral bommie.

Tetepare. The mosaic was set up on the point just outside the small bay. The shoreward bearing is 180 degrees and the center pins are oriented in a 260/90 degree bearing. Top right corner was set directly on top of a large thicket of Acropora.

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Bodu Fulhadhoo. ** NO FISH SURVEYS PAIRED WITH THIS MOSAIC. CALIBRATION SHOTS FOR 18 mm camera were taken trying to fit lasers on the board - potentially far away and out of focus. Only one GPS point on NW Corner (white stripe) due to GPS malfunction and confusion with boat drivers. Mosaic collected ~15:30 and water was murky. Could be dark. Short wall defines the eastern edge of the plot and reef drops off quickly at S and W edges. Beyond the N edge is a large field of Goniopora and a small Acropora thicket. Lots of overlap in deep side of plot but shallow side done quickly. Plot size odd due to need to fit in this particular spot

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Velidhu. CALIBRATION SHOTS FOR 18 mm camera were taken trying to fit lasers on the board - potentially far away and out of focus. CCA very pale - see site photos. No diagonal mesurements in shallow due to difficulty staying outside camera FOV on steep slope and time constraints. Mosaic collected after 16:00. Conditions dark and lots of damsels/chromis in the acropora...could be a problem for image assembly. 55 mm stuck in A-F mode not A-Fc

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes:
Vihamaafaru. CALIBRATION SHOTS FOR 18 mm camera were taken trying to fit lasers on the board - potentially far away and out of focus. see datasheet for drawings. S edge defined by sand patch and large P. lobata. E edge defined by 2 small rises in topography. W edge parallel to drop off. Large dead P. lobata at N center of plot 
Second set of passes made in large swathes...final pass made parallel to western boarder (in line with 1st set of passes)  Lots of soft corals and zooanthid. Black spong-like creature in NW corner is actually a nudibranch

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Feridoo. Condensation of drops inside dome of the 18 but focus was OK and couldn't see drops on live view...double checked raw images and looked OK too. See original datasheet for drawings of distinguishing features

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Maalhos. Extra GPS at large Acropora ~ 10 m away at 160 deg. from SE corner (W |) N 3.98590, E 72.70915

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Kandholhudhoo. Plot is steep and deep with lots of Acropora. Tried to get center line as close to 10 m mark as possible. See datasheet for drawings of identifying landmarks. Fake piece of pineapple top or something in one of the acroporas - not an organism. See site photos. Lrg Physogyra colony ~10m at 120ish from S center pin across field of sand and rubble. Plot very steep but good flying with extra up and down passes

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Meerufengfushi. See datasheet for drawings of identifying landmarks. Plot exceptionally steep but made bottom extra wide to try and cope with any warping or distortion. Plot well defined by 2 sand scars. but habitat is very fragile and suceptible to damage. large P. lobata in SW sector of plot will be good long-term reference point

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Vihamaafaru. Fore reef uninhabited - second site on this island (1.2 km north of first). Current running east ~0.25 knts and slight swell. Lots of reef fish in plot. Use two acropora tables in center of plot to site the center line...falls right between them (live on on S side, dead on N). Sand channel beyond Y + and 2 large dead P. lobata beyond SW center

Mosaic Divers: M. Fox, K. Furby, B. Zgliczynski
Mosaic Notes: Rasdhoo. GPS points are rough - unit failed to save points due to "poor connection" so hand recorded them. Look for the P. lobata in the channel (see datasheet). Channel ~10 m south of the plot and porities about 5-8 m up the channel to the east. Black/Gray corals have been taken over by a sponge. Long diagonal due to depth bed in plot...measured it twice

Mosaic Notes: CREP CAU site. Not oriented alongshore> from reference stake (p6 location tile) to p3 is inshore and p5 to p1 is alongshore. Abnormal CAU setup likely due to reef area with big acropora thickets. Just setup as normal but inshore instead of alongshore.

Ocean Conditions: Good lighting but cloud cover towards end of dive, no surge, no current
Mosaic Notes: resurvey of CREP CAU site,no current, vis was ok but pretty hazy. Very steep slope. CAUs in one long line because of this on sam isobath. The plot starts at the location of the first CAU going right alongshore. There was also a refernce stake right next to it. pretty easy site to setup/see due to big coral head by reference stake/first CAU and corallimorph field near p1 tile.

Ocean Conditions: Ok vis ~ 10m, no current, slight surge, good lighting
Mosaic Notes: The non-reference stake stake looked a bit suspect becasue it was not in very far, so that may be gone upon return.

Ocean Conditions: Ok vis ~ 10m, no current, slight surge, good lighting
Mosaic Notes: Lots of corallimorph. Looks like it is coming from deep and taking over. Will be interesting to see if it continues in the future.

Ocean Conditions: Steep, slope, no surge, slight current ~10m vis
Mosaic Notes: CAUs in one straight line beginning with 1st CAU @ p6 tile or what would be the reference stake for our normal set up. This site did not have a CREP reference stake, just started line with first CAU.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, med surge, med current, good vis ~15m
Mosaic Notes: CAUs not in perfect 5 x 10m which resulted in large plot, sorry. The p6 tile is right at the reference stake though. Had to adjust the plot so dont fully go off these bearings. Saw a hammerhead, yew!

Ocean Conditions: Good light, med surge, strong current
Mosaic Notes: Cau site but not a normal setup. Make sure to study roda map well. There was no reference stake found so used the dead coral head with zip ties wrapped around it as the reference stake spot. I chose the best 10 x 10m area that I could imagine would encompass the most CAUs. Be aware that this area of the island if known for having a strong current and plan accordingly.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, strong surge, slight current
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Lots of acropora on sides makes it hard to re-set tiles but think I did well. Looks like site gets pretty hammered. Original site from 2017 was setup up large and tried to resurvey entire area. For next visit might be worth while to shorten the non-refernce stake side to make it easier/faster dive. One caus is just outside of the plot a few meters to the left fo the p6 tile ( if looking towards shore). This CAU will likely not show up in model.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis ~ 100ft, no current, no surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. CAU site was setup properly. The reference stake is very hidden because completely overgrown with CCA. Relatively flat compared to most of these small island sites.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis ~ 100ft, no current, small surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU site, setup properly with reference stake there.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis ~ 100ft, slight current, slight surge
Mosaic Notes: This is a CAU site. it is not setup normal. It is a striaght line setup due to the fact that the reef drops off quickly/dramatically as you go deeper from the CAUs. For this reason the mosaic site was set up unique. The reference stake is down by the P1 tile (as opposed to the normal P6 tile location) and the CAUs run along the deep/offshore edge of the transect from P1 --> P2. The site is then a 10x10m box in shore of this.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis ~ 200ft, slight current, no surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Normal CAU 5 x 10m setup. Reference stake with zip tie.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, slight current, great vis ~200ft
Mosaic Notes: Was a CAU site but they pulled all the CAUs and only left the reference stake and the P3  tile location stake for when we revisit. They did not deploy new CAUs as this site is being scrapped as a CAU site in the future since they already have 4 at this island in the cardinal direction locations.

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis ~200ft, slight surge, slight current
Mosaic Notes: New site, we installed a reference stake with locking nut and other stake at P3 tile location. Large lobata in the plot near the reference stake. Best thing to use to find this site. Pretty awesome site aesthetically

Ocean Conditions: Good light, good vis ~100ft, no surge, med. to strong current
Mosaic Notes: New site, we installed a reference stake with locking nut and other stake at P3 tile location

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, H. Barkley, C. Klepac
Ocean Conditions: Low light (overcast), meh vis (~50ft, but hazy), lots of surge (8ft seas above), no current
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Reference stake was missing, so OCC team installed new reference stake 5m up slope from CAU tiles, since they weren't sure if the stake disappeared or the CAUS were installed in straight line due to slope. Upper left corner of plot is quite high up on a ledge bc of orientation of plot.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, C. Klepac, H. Barkley
Ocean Conditions: Good light, good vis ~60ft, lots of surge and light current
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. OCC team set up plot, 3 ARMS & all caus are in the bottom half of the plot, 1 CAU may be slightly outside bottom border of plot. Forgot the GoPro on charger, so there's no GoPro footage from this site. Dive was cut short by ~10 min because buddy was low on air, so the left side of the plot may have some holes and/or trouble aligning. I tried to get as much overlap as I could on my last pass and flew a little higher to compensate.

Ocean Conditions: Overcast, dark, hazy viz ~30ft, very little surge or current
Mosaic Notes: NOAA ARMS & CAU site. Lots of instruments deployed at this site (bottom half of plot). Top left corner is at the edge of a very tall rock/ bommie. There's a channel on the far right side of the plot, and the right markers are on the adjacent ridge. No GoPro.

Ocean Conditions: Overcast, dark, hazy viz ~40ft, very little surge or current
Mosaic Notes: CAU Site. Plot was set up by H. Barkley and C. Klepac, finished by A. Halperin. Plot is oriented facing the side of the bay/cove, not the village (this was not intuitive for me). Caus are along the center line of the plot with two randomly spaced in bottom half of plot. Spur and groove reef with relatively constant depth & sand pits throughout.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Overcast, a little surge, current at top of rock face
Mosaic Notes: CAU Site. Geology was quite complex with big walls. CAU site set up in a line at the bottom of the plot, but all CAUs were removed, as this site will no longer be used by NOAA. CAU stake and reference stake were left behind and mark the two bottom corners of the plot, NOT the center points! Very important - the stake does not indicate a left/ center reference point! There is a big lobata colony adjacent to bottom right pin that has a series of small hole punches sampled by microbe team. Also, there are only 3 calibration sticks because one was lost on dive 1.

Ocean Conditions: Overcast, some surge/ current, decent vis
Mosaic Notes: CAU site removed on this dive. Really cool wall of P. rus that flattens out around 12m to rubble field. Look for reference stake at bottom of wall (there was a subsurface float near it that we left in place, but don't count on it being there for future visits).

Ocean Conditions: Overcast, lots of surge (super annoying), some current, good vis ~60ft
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Neat wall with lots of charismatic corals (Acropora tables, Diploastrea, Turbinaria, Lobophyllia). Ref stake is in bottom left of plot because the CAU line was quite deep (~13m). Bottom half of plot is steeper than top half.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, H. Barkley, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Overcast, dark, no current, some surge, vis ~80ft
Mosaic Notes: CAU & ARMS site. Lots of big charismatic coral colonies (massive brain coral right in the middle, bit acropora table in bottom half). CAUS make a line across the midline from the ref stake (14.6m) and another line across the bottom border of plot.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Overcast, dark, no current, some surge, vis ~80ft
Mosaic Notes: CAU site removed on this dive. Really interesting 3D structure here, lots of encrusting & plating corals (lots of broken up echinopora) with a cavern-like hole in the middle that's difficult to get the rig in/ around. This site definitely took a little longer than others due to the complexity. Left side of plot is against a short ridge/ wall, right side ends just before a slope/ ridge.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, H. Barkley, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Overcast, dark, some surge, good vis ~80ft
Mosaic Notes: CAU & ARMS site. This plot is quite deep (ref stake at 15m). A few big porites and gradual slope. CAUS make a line across the midline from the ref stake (14.9m) and another line across the bottom border of plot.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun, A. Halperin
Ocean Conditions: Finally sunshine! Great vis ~100ft, annoying current ~.5kt, and lots of surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU & ARMS site. Low relief slope, no large coral features, mostly pavement. I think the tides and currents here get pretty gnarly & the reef is quite exposed. Big ridge to the left of plot, and another large feature just outside the bottom right corner. CAUS make a line across the midline from the ref stake (14.6m) and another line across the bottom border of plot.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Very little current, some surge, incredible vis (>100'), sunny
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Strong current at "deep STR" site (down slope ~20m) was misleading, so dove with just the 18mm camera to avoid over exertion. Swam a little closer to reef and slower than usual to make up for lacking 55mm cam. Site was complex with lots of interesting structure and lots of really cool corals (some relatively uncommon). Really cool site! Ref stake is at bottom left corner of plot bc of depth and structure.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Great vis, good lighting (partly sunny), no current and very little surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Ref stake at bottom left corner of plot. Big crevice/ valley down the middle of plot with lots of really cool, uncommon corals. Some really cool big Diploastrea colonies border the plot. Super interesting site! Also, saw octopuses out and about mating at this site.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, B. Vargas, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Incredible vis, no current or surge, great lighting
Mosaic Notes: CAU and ARMS site. Combo of ridges and rubble channels. Big pinnacle just outside of lower right corner with lots of fire coral on top. Top right target may be too far out for plot- definitely not square, sorry.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, B. Vargas, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Incredible vis, no current or surge, great lighting
Mosaic Notes: This was an opportunistic grab on a fun dive. Only took down the 18mm with 4 targets and 2 calibration sticks. Swam around Big Mama in an upward spiral, starting near the bottom left (facing shore) and working upward in ~15 min.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Good lighting & great vis (>80ft), fairly strong current (~.5kt)
Mosaic Notes: CAU and ARMS site. Relatively flat reef, not a lot of structure or notable features. GoPro video was stopped halfway through for technical difficulties restarting interval timer - one of the cameras was loose in the housing and had to be tilted upward to press buttons.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Good lighting & incredible vis (>100), flat calm with no current or surge
Mosaic Notes: CAU site, setup properly with reference stake there. Plot bordered by large P. lobata bommies.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, H. Barkley, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Great lighting, partly cloudy, suuuuper surgey in shallower depths but ok in plot, bonkers vis (~150' basically could see forever)
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Ref stake middle of plot at 15m. Not many notable features.

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Great lighting, partly cloudy, very little surge, no current, great vis to infinity and beyond
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Ref stake at left middle tile, 12.6m. Large massive Pavona in bottom right corner, and giant yellow foliose Turbinaria outside plot to bottom right. Incredible CCA pillars that look like sand castles EVERYWHERE! SO COOL!

Mosaic Divers: S. Clements, A. Halperin, C. Klepac, S. Calhoun
Ocean Conditions: Decent lighting, partly cloudy, against a rock wall that reflects swell so the surge was like a washing machine
Mosaic Notes: CAU site. Ref stake at left middle tile. Decent sized P. lobata in middle of plot, but not a lot of notable features otherwise. Bottom left corner may be cut short because of air consumption. Also, may be some diver interference due to dive buddy swimming beneath cameras.

Mosaic Divers: N. Pedersen, C. Klepac, T. Oliver, K. Green
Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis, no current or surge
Fly Patterns: Double lawn mower, second lawn was a little fast-buddy air limitations cut the dive short
Mosaic Notes: CAU and ARMS site, steep slope, big bommie in middle of plot

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis, no current or surge
Mosaic Notes: New established site, installed two stakes, fairly flat, saw a manta! GPS point taken over PAM float, may not be exactly over reference stake but should be in close general area

Mosaic Notes: CAU site, super rubbly, all but one CAU had no tiles, reinstalled reference stake

Mosaic Notes: CAU & ARMs site, super rubbly, missed one depth measurement

Ocean Conditions: Good light, great vis, moderate surge
Mosaic Notes: New established site, installed two stakes, pretty shallow reef area, swam a bit to find the deepest area-were trying to overlap with previous benthic survey, but that site was at ~20ft so kept swimming for deeper area. Flight pattern may be slightly wonky during middle of imaging, was super distracted by pod of dolphins...
